onboardings.intro.config.content: Task interface editor. The interface is in JSON format. The editor provides auto-complete with hints and code snippets.
onboardings.intro.config.title: Config
onboardings.intro.documentation.content: Go to our guide to find examples, instructions, and a reference list of components with descriptions.
onboardings.intro.documentation.title: Tutorials and help
onboardings.intro.fullscreen.content: Expands the editor to full screen.
onboardings.intro.fullscreen.title: Full-screen mode
onboardings.intro.input.content:
Editor for JSON input data. Paste an example of input data here, like text or a link to an image. You will immediately see it in the interface.

Toloka uses the input data sample to generate a specification.
onboardings.intro.input.title: Sample input data
onboardings.intro.preview.content: See the interface preview and test it with your own data. If there are any errors, you'll see their cause here.
onboardings.intro.preview.title: Preview
onboardings.intro.toggle-input.content:
You can show or hide the Configuration, Sample input, and Preview panels. 

The panel with the results (output data) will appear when you click "Submit" in the preview. You can also close this panel using a separate button at the bottom of the panel.
onboardings.intro.toggle-input.title: Buttons to show/hide panels
output.outdated: Click  "Submit" to refresh the data in the Preview.
